An attacker can pass any value to this function and it will be re-assigned to `value` but it won't change `maxWallet`. As a result, no matter how large the input is, `maxWallet` will remain unchanged. This could lead to a situation where users are unable to add their tokens to their wallets because `maxWallet` is too small.

